# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the HotChick restaurant project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package to the project dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` with the new dependency

### 2. Modified Files
- **src/App.tsx**:
  - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/react";`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the component tree, just before closing the `TooltipProvider`
  - The component is placed at the app root level to track all page views and routes

## Implementation Details

This is a Vite + React + TypeScript project using React Router for navigation. Following the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications, I:

1. Installed the `@vercel/analytics` package using npm
2. Added the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react` 
3. Placed it in the main App component to ensure it tracks all routes and page views

The Analytics component is a wrapper around the tracking script that offers seamless integration with React. It will automatically track page views when deployed to Vercel.

## Verification

- ✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
- ✅ No linting errors introduced in the modified file (App.tsx)
- ✅ All dependencies properly installed and lock file updated

## Next Steps

After deploying to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics tab
4. Look for `/_vercel/insights/view` requests in the browser's Network tab to verify proper setup
